biography arno kourula d sc econ is a postdoctoral fellow at stanford university's department for civil and environmental engineering his research in the field of international business has focused on corporate responsibility the relationship between nongovernmental organizations and business stakeholder management and relations and base of the pyramid bop business models arno defended his phd entitled company engagement with nongovernmental organizations from a corporate responsibility perspective at the helsinki school of economics in 2009 currently known as aalto university school of economics for the past year he has been the project manager at aalto university in a research project examining packaging mass communication and primary education practices of low income individuals and households in india russia tanzania and brazil in addition to publishing in various international business and business and society journals arno has taught courses and organized seminars on corporate responsibility and business ethics at the bachelor master doctoral and executive education levels
